	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One thing I forgot to mention. I believe there's a confusion regarding the <em>backbuffer</em> (a bitmap) and the <em>screen</em> (<span style="text-decoration: underline">the hardware itself</span>). So, I don't see any visible distortions in the PPU output while manipulating pixels in the backbuffer; the data transfer to the screen is done by <strong>blit()</strong>, and yes, the way how it does isn't interesting to me, since the library (Allegro) handles it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


